Please note that this may require some modification on some clones and models. I have it installed on a Taurus PT1911 and although it is a tight fit it does work and looks really good. Please don't bid if you are unwilling to modify this if need be. It is a very tight fit.

This is a brand new muzzle brake which will fit colt 1911 model pistols and most 1911 clones. It replaces the barrel bushing and usually installs in less than a minute. This design is contoured to mimic the front of the slide, and give the appearance of having an extended slide.

This is made to work with full size 1911 models. It is a little tight but does work

The short slide 1911 pistols such as the commander series, will require that the comp be modified to fit. This involves trimming down the bushing section of the comp to match the length of the original barrel bushing.

Please note before ordering:

The bushing ID. Is .583" +-.0005". In general they will fit any 1911 clone pistol that has a barrel OD. between .577"-581".

Also this comp will not work on Commander short length 1911's unless it is fitted. This involves trimming down the length of the bushing section of the comp, to match the length of the original barrel bushing.

title: For Sale/Trade:  PMAG - Ammo
postcontent:
description
I have quite a few 30 rd PMAGS (non window) black...

I really would like to add some ammo to my collection.

I need .223 .... 7.62 ..... 40 cal....... 9mm

Now, Im willing to be reasonable on values. PMAGS normally go for $12 - $20
Most are asking $40 - $75 now a days!!!!

If you are willing to price your ammo right, I'll price my mags right. I am well versed on ammo prices, both before and after the big O screwed things up 

Here is my reference guide for normal ammo prices. (S) = steel and (B) = brass
.223 = .20/.25 per rd (S) to .35/.40 per rd (B)
7.62 = .20 to .25 per rd (prefer S)
9mm = .20/.22 per rd (S) to .25/.27 per rd (B)
.40cal = .26/.27 per rd (S) to .30/.33 per rd (B)

We are all lovers of this wonderful hobby of being gun enthusiasts....so let's stick together and treat each other fairly.
